<p>The <code>flag</code> tag sets a flag during iteration.</p>

<h2>Basic Flag</h2>
<pre>{open}sequence 5, name='i'{close}
  {open}if $i eq 3{close}
    {open}flag 'found'{close}
  {open}/if{close}
{open}/sequence{close}
{open}if $found{close}Found 3!{open}/if{close}</pre>
{sequence 5, name='i'}
  {if $i eq 3}
    {flag 'found'}
  {/if}
{/sequence}
{if $found eq 1}
<p style="color:green">Found 3!</p>
{/if}

<h2>Flag for Detection</h2>
<p>Flags are useful to detect if a condition was met during iteration.</p>
<pre>{open}items{close}
  {open}if $status eq 'error'{close}
    {open}flag 'hasErrors'{close}
  {open}/if{close}
{open}/items{close}
{open}if $hasErrors{close}
  Warning: Errors detected!
{open}/if{close}</pre>
